From f427506becff95be16d7dd1920dc3033217102f0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Justin Suess <utilityemal77@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 17:34:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 02/14] clk: sunxi-ng: sun55i-a523: keep the IOMMU clock always
 on

The IOMMU sits in the memory fabric between the display/video masters and
DRAM. Even when it is not used for translation (the DE uses raw physical
addresses in mainline), master traffic still passes through it, so its
functional clock must stay on or DE fetches come back corrupted.

Nothing claims the clock yet, so clk_disable_unused() gates it at boot and
display fetches return garbage unless clk_ignore_unused is passed on the
cmdline. Mark it CLK_IS_CRITICAL as a stop-gap until an IOMMU driver
manages it.

This is a hack, but it works for now (alternative is cmd boot option
clk_ignore unused)
---
 drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun55i-a523.c | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun55i-a523.c b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun55i-a523.c
index 7997a26645de..26e35caae7a0 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun55i-a523.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun55i-a523.c
@@ -584,13 +584,22 @@ static const struct clk_parent_data iommu_parents[] = {
 	{ .fw_name = "hosc" },
 };
 
+/*
+ * The IOMMU sits in the memory fabric between the display/video masters and
+ * DRAM. Even when it is not used for translation (the DE uses raw physical
+ * addresses in mainline), the master traffic still passes through it, so its
+ * functional clock must stay on or DE fetches come back corrupted. Nothing
+ * claims it yet, so mark it critical to keep clk_disable_unused() from gating
+ * it (otherwise boards need clk_ignore_unused on the cmdline). Proper fix is
+ * to manage it from an IOMMU driver.
+ */
 static SUNXI_CCU_MP_DATA_WITH_MUX_GATE_FEAT(iommu_clk, "iommu", iommu_parents,
 					    0x7b0,
 					    0, 5,	/* M */
 					    0, 0,	/* no P */
 					    24, 3,	/* mux */
 					    BIT(31),	/* gate */
-					    CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT,
+					    CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT | CLK_IS_CRITICAL,
 					    CCU_FEATURE_UPDATE_BIT);
 
 static SUNXI_CCU_GATE_HWS(bus_iommu_clk, "bus-iommu", apb0_hws, 0x7bc,
